problem:
Coplanar squares $ABGH$ and $BCDF$ are adjacent, with $CD = 401310$ units and $AH = 637$ units. Point $E$ is on segments $AD$ and $GB$. What is the area of triangle $ABE$, in square units? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(637,0)--(637,637)--(0,637)--(0,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));
draw((637,0)--(401947,0)--(401947,401310)--(637,401310)--(637,0)--cycle,linewidth(2));

draw((0,0)--(401947,401310),linewidth(2));

filldraw((0,0)--(637,0)--(637,401310/631)--(0,0)--cycle,gray,linewidth(2));

label("A",(0,0),SW);
label("B",(637,0),S);
label("C",(401947,0),SE);
label("D",(401947,401310),NE);
label("E",(637,401310/631),SE);
label("F",(637,401310),NW);
label("G",(637,637),NW);
label("H",(0,637),NW);
[/asy]
